<br>
The skeleton's spawn is incredibly close to the zone in from EJ.  The problem is it's up the wall and to the right of the zone.  The only way to get to the skel is either grav fluxing someone up the wall, or doing it the hard way. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
The hard way is fighting your way to Mist Castle.  Before you get to Mist Castle, you will definitely run into some reavers.<br>
<br>
Check Graffe's spoiler for some maps. <p><BR>
<A HREF="mailto:baedm@hotmail.com">Baedm Solarrian</A><BR><A HREF="http://pub26.ezboard.com/borderofthescatteredwinds">Order of the Scattered Winds</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.portice.com/berthall">Bertoxxulous</A></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=aelina>Aelina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 126<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/15/01 8:34 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Human Skeleton in CoM for Brain Bite</span><hr size=1> Baedm is exactly right.  If you use Grav flux to get to the skell black reavers are not a concern.  If you try to get there with out using grav flux you must go through two black reaver spawn points.  Which means an indeterminate number of black reavers and at least two Lords.  Unless you have at least 18 people about level 50+ I strongly advise against trying to get to him without grav flux. <p><table cellpadding=0 cellspacing=0><tr><td>Aelina</td></tr>
<tr><td>Wizard of Neriak</td></tr>
<tr><td>Follower of The Burning Prince</td></tr>
<tr><td>Ayonae Ro</td></tr></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/udolomite.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dolomite</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/16/01 10:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skeleton</span><hr size=1> I found the ONLY way to get him is to use Grav Flux. Have a group hang out at the bridge.. pull the area clear of spawns.. the bridge, behind the gate and along the right side there on the ledge.  As soon as its clear, buff yourself all up, grav flux up to the upper ledge.. run around aggro the heck out of the skeleton.. Jump into the water near the bridge from where you came.. and get onto land near the bridge.  Soon enough the skeleton and some of his buddies will be on their way.  In general you might pull 3-4 mobs if you cleared the way pretty well.<br>
<br>
If the Skeleton is up, you will hear/see him casting buffs on himself.  If you don't hear it in the area of the bridge.. then his PH is up.  I suggest doing a Grav Flux pull of the PH and any crap thats up top.. kill all of the mobs that come.. and wait for him to spawn.  I forget now.. its either 20 minutes or 40 minutes for the respawn.<br>
<br>
This is something I found out the hard way..<br>
<br>
If the COM Human Skeleton is Mezzed and Charmed.. he will not accept the bottle from you!  He needs to be Charmed BUT NOT Mezzed.  I had the darn skeleton in front of me charmed and mezzed.. lo and behold some other wizard shows up and and stands right next to him.. my assumption was to try to steal the spawn from my group by giving the bottle in.  So.. I was going click crazy with the bottle and finished the quest the moment he unmezzed.  He nukes pretty hard too, so be careful (maybe 45th level wizard).<br>
<br>
Good luck! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=kazzap>Kazzap</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 14<br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/28/01 11:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skeleton</span><hr size=1> Thank you for the tips on the CoM skellie. <p><img src="http://www.geocities.com/tendeep/bar07.gif"><br>
