<br>
To make sure you're killing the right mobs, I'll give you some directions.  If you face the main gates at CoM while standing on the bridge, look up.  On the top of the wall is a path where mobs roam.  Follow the top of the wall with your eyes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> to your right</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> as far as you possible can.  Once you stop following the wall, you should be facing at a 90 degree angle too the gates, with the gates to your left.  Right at this point is a door (you can't see it from the ground.  Just inside the door, is 3 mobs.  The &quot;a human skeleton&quot; spawns in one of these places.  Sorry, I don't remember which spot he/she specifically spawns in.  It's been a long time since I did the quest.<br>
<br>
I used bind sight to learn the tops of the walls in CoM.  I bound sight to the wanderers up there.  It worked well.<br>
<br>
Last weekend, I did a raid to CoM with my guild.  While fighting the first reaver, our pullers were able to pull the skeleton.  If you can't do the grav flux method, bring 2 groups of 50ish people and start killing.  Fight your way to the &quot;camp point&quot; right before the Mist Castle and the &quot;a human skeleton&quot; should be more accessible. <p><BR>
<A HREF="mailto:baedm@hotmail.com">Baedm Solarrian</A><BR><A HREF="http://pub26.ezboard.com/borderofthescatteredwinds">Order of the Scattered Winds</A><BR><A HREF="http://www.portice.com/berthall">Bertoxxulous</A><BR>
<i>I've got a FEVER, and the only PRESCRIPTION is more COWBELL!</i></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/unlaren.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nlaren</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/8/01 11:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Human Skeleton in CoM for Brain Bite</span><hr size=1> Well using Bind/Shifting Sight would have been the way to go to learn the area pre NERF.  But since they changed these spells recently, you cant recast over and over to hop around the zone.  You have to be able to see your target from YOUR eyes and not from the mob that you are currently sight bound to.  This makes things that much more fun when trying to do this quest.  I used Shifting Sight when I did the Karnors part to check for the roamers on the landing zone.  I tried it a few nights ago after the change and I was unable to bind sight on anything up there.  I also couldn't transfer the bind like you used to be able to do.<br>
<br>
One more thing to make us wizards happy...<br>
<br>
