<br>
I have completed this quest already, I was simply pointing out that the old trick of using bind sight to check the path or verify that the skel is up will no longer work.  I did this quest when it was possible to bind sight and transfer your bind from mob to mob throughout the entire zone.  This made things extremely easy to verify if the human skeleton was up or if you were going to be in for some PH killing.<br>
<br>
OFF TOPIC: I also liked to use Bind sight in Kithicor Forest at night while waiting to go through the zone.  Just a time waster really, but I could get from one side of the zone to the other using bind sight.  After the changes, you can only bind to a mob if you can see it directly.  I think this drastically reduces the use of this spell.  Why would you want to bind sight to something you can see anyway?  The only reason I would do that was to rebind to something I couldn't see to extend my sight that much further.  This is no longer possible.  That is what I was attempting to say. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uaarani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aarani</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 25<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/8/01 3:16 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Human Skeleton in CoM for Brain Bite</span><hr size=1> Ah, ok.  Sorry.  Missed the point there, Nlaren <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  However, even though you can't bind sight, when you're on the bridge you should see the spell casting messages for the human skeleton.  At least that was the case when I was there <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
