<br>
I am one of those 40-ish Wizards who would like to get this spell now despite the fact that everyone says it's intended for higher-level play. I have a 50 Bard guildmate who can charm it for me, but we are a little low on enchanters and wizards who can Grav Flux (none in fact).<br>
<br>
After reading every post on this board(and others) about getting the CoM Skel, I have a theory for a new way to pull it - without Grav Flux - that I want to run by my fellow wizards.<br>
<br>
It has been said elsewhere that by standing on the bridge and furiously clicking the base of the tower, you can actually target the static spawn that stands opposite the human skel. <br>
<br>
What I would like to try is this: After clearing bridge/courtyard area with a full group, I target this mob, and my group moves to the ledge below the skel room. I would then stand as close to the wall as possible and cast a PBAE spell like Thunderclap. Group moves back to bridge, and we wait for mobs to come kill me<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  If it did work, it would be almsot certain death for me, but that would be worth it to me to get this spell, and easier than finding a volunteer wiz or enc to grav flux another volunteer up to the wall.<br>
<br>
Any thoughts on whether or not this would work? Could I Bind Sight to the mob first to make sure no other spawns wander by when I cast? The gods know I have hit both intended and unintended targets thru walls(hermit in SK) and above and below me(Najena, Aviak treehouse,&lt;insert dungeon name here&gt;  before...<br>
<br>
Anyway, if I am cracked tell me so<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  But if any fellow wizards think this might even have a remote possibility of success, I am going to try it.  <p><FONT SIZE="-3">Invectus Stormborn<BR>
